                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d829">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.937/23: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-06-27T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >June 27, 1929—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 27—9:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>515. Department’s mail instruction No. 1223, May 18th. In view of Legation’s
                    instruction of April 22nd to Hankow, copies of which were forwarded to the
                    Department without covering despatch April 28th, is it desired that the Legation
                    take any action at this juncture?</p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hewes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
